  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.82,
      "end": 8.76,
      "text": "This is a Libervox recording. All Libervox recordings are in the public domain. For more",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 8.76,
      "end": 14.2,
      "text": "information, or to volunteer, please visit Libervox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 16.46,
      "end": 20.84,
      "text": "ESOPS FABLES, THE FROGS ASKING FOR A KING",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 22.68,
      "end": 29.4,
      "text": "Time was when the frogs were discontented because they had no one to rule over them. So they",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 29.4,
      "end": 36.78,
      "text": "sent a deputation to Jupiter to ask him to give them a king. Jupiter, despising the",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 36.78,
      "end": 42.36,
      "text": "folly of their request, cast a log into the pool where they lived, and said that that",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 42.36,
      "end": 48.52,
      "text": "should be their king. The frogs were terrified at first by the splash, and scuttled away",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 48.52,
      "end": 54.74,
      "text": "into the deepest parts of the pool. But by and by, when they saw that the log remained",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 54.74,
      "end": 62.04,
      "text": "motionless, one by one, they ventured to the surface again, and before long, growing bolder,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 62.54,
      "end": 67.08,
      "text": "they began to feel such contempt for it that they even took to sitting upon it.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 67.86,
      "end": 73.98,
      "text": "Thinking that a king of that sort was an insult to their dignity. They sent to Jupiter a second time,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 74.74,
      "end": 80.74,
      "text": "and begged him to take away the sluggish king he had given them, and to give them another and a",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 80.92,
      "end": 87.78,
      "text": "better one. Jupiter, annoyed at being pestered in this way, sent a stalk to rule over them,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 88.52,
      "end": 94.24,
      "text": "who no sooner arrived among them than he began to catch and eat the frogs as fast as he could.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 96.56,
      "end": 99.9,
      "text": "End of THE FROGS ASKING FOR A KING",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
